{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"677479f0-dbe4-4e84-9637-58bf1dd84279","content":"In an `MSTest.Sdk` project, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is actually the **default**. VSTest is the opt-in. To switch:\n\n### 1. Remove the VSTest opt-in\n\nIn your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove or set to false -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nSimply deleting that line is enough — `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0` defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `<UseVSTest>` is absent or `false`.\n\n### 2. Run tests\n\n```bash\n# Works the same way\ndotnet test\n```\n\n### 3. Watch for breaking changes\n\n- **CLI output format** changes (different progress/summary display).\n- **`.runsettings`** — most settings still work, but some VSTest-specific ones (e.g., custom adapters) won't apply.\n- **Test filters** use `--filter` the same way, but the underlying engine differs.\n- If you use `dotnet test --logger`, verify your loggers are compatible with the new platform.\n\nThat's it — since you're already on `MSTest.Sdk`, no package reference changes are needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"65817033-ec44-476d-94cf-36f64cb9623e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a general knowledge question about .NET testing configuration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nWhen using MSTest.Sdk, switching from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform involves:\n\n1. Removing or setting `<UseVSTest>false</UseVSTest>` (since Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default in newer MSTest.Sdk versions)\n2. Potentially updating the SDK version\n3. Being aware of CLI differences (`dotnet test` vs `dotnet run`)\n\nLet me give a concise answer.","outputTokens":449,"requestId":"1BED:2F4A2A:205AAB5:23BEC90:6A03CE79"},"id":"d248f6ee-8b77-443a-a8f6-85466882bd74","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:06:12.942Z","parentId":"c0bc2ef3-f9c8-48e8-a16e-f3ba43232c20"}
